multiflexi-microsoft365 (0.1.0) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  * Initial release: Office 365 / SharePoint credential prototype split out of
    php-vitexsoftware-multiflexi-core into its own add-on package.
  * Two binary packages: multiflexi-microsoft365 (core) and
    multiflexi-microsoft365-ui (web interface).
  * checkAvailability(): two-phase connection check (acquire token, then a real
    SharePoint REST call) built on vgrem/php-spo; prefers Entra ID v2
    client_credentials with legacy ACS fallback; distinguishes transient from
    permanent failures and never logs the client secret.
  * postinst runs multiflexi-cli credential-prototype:sync.
  * Add EntraIdAppOnlyAuthenticationContext and wire it into
    SharePointConnector::sharePointContext() so real data operations (not
    just the diagnostic probe) authenticate via the Entra ID v2 app-only
    client_credentials flow for the client-id/secret case. Previously
    sharePointContext()/verify() phase two always built the ClientContext
    via the legacy Azure ACS ClientCredential/withCredentials() SDK path
    regardless of what the v2 probe found - meaning even when v2 auth
    worked, real SharePoint calls still went through the ACS flow Microsoft
    fully retired on 2026-04-02 and would fail. withSharePointRetry()'s
    second parameter is generalized from ACS-specific credentials to a
    plain reset callback (see resetAuthCallback()) accordingly.
  * Surface expiry information in ProbeResult::$details and the credential
    UI: the acquired Entra ID v2 token's expiry (reliable), and a
    best-effort lookup of the app registration's client secret expiry via
    Microsoft Graph (requires the app to additionally hold the
    "Application.Read.All" Graph application permission - reported as
    "unknown" rather than an error when that permission is absent, which is
    the common case for SharePoint-only app registrations).
  * Fix: stop requiring OFFICE365_SITE on the credential itself. It only
    makes sense for SharePoint access, is commonly supplied per-runtemplate
    instead (e.g. one bank-statement runtemplate per SharePoint folder,
    sharing one Office365 credential across many runtemplates/sites), and
    has no meaning at all for non-SharePoint Microsoft 365 services this
    credential type may also back. Previously missingRequiredFields()
    reported OFFICE365_SITE missing whenever it wasn't set on the
    credential, which checkAvailability() surfaced as Misconfigured -
    multiflexi-executor 1.18.0's new Phase 2 credential gate then hard-
    blocked every job using such a credential (confirmed in production:
    "blocked by credential Daramis Office365 (misconfigured): Required
    fields not set: OFFICE365_SITE", even though the credential's
    tenant/client id/secret were entirely valid). verify() now reports the
    Phase 1 (token) result alone when no site is configured, rather than
    treating "no site" as a failure; also removed the field-level
    setRequired(true) on OFFICE365_SITE for the same reason.
  * verify()'s phase-two check for the client-id/secret (app-only) case now
    goes through Microsoft Graph (new verifyViaGraph()) instead of classic
    SharePoint REST (sharePointContext(), what it used before). Switching
    only the token source to Entra ID v2 (above) was not enough: classic
    SharePoint REST checks the token's appidacr claim and requires
    appidacr=2 (certificate-based app-only auth) - a client_credentials
    token obtained with a client *secret* always has appidacr=1 and is
    unconditionally rejected with "Unsupported app only token.", regardless
    of Sites.Selected permissions granted. Confirmed empirically against a
    real tenant: the exact same token/app/site that gets HTTP 200 from
    Microsoft Graph gets HTTP 401 from _api/web/title. See
    https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/blog/microsoftmissioncriticalblog/avoiding-access-errors-with-sharepoint-app-only-access/4459761
    This package is diagnostic-only (no file upload/list here), so the fix
    is just making the check reflect the transport real consumers (e.g.
    pohoda-raiffeisenbank) actually use. The user-credential flow is
    unaffected and keeps using classic REST via sharePointContext().
    EntraIdAppOnlyAuthenticationContext gains getBearerToken() for this
    (returns the raw token for direct Graph calls, rather than only via the
    SDK's RequestOptions-based authenticateRequest()).

 -- Vitex <info@vitexsoftware.cz>  Tue, 07 Jul 2026 10:00:00 +0200
